Crassispira incrassata, common name the thickened pleurotoma, is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pseudomelatomidae.ITIS considers Crassispira bottae a synonym of Crassispira incrassata  McLean confirmed that Pleurotoma bottae was a synonym of Crassispira incrassata  The radula and the morphology was studied by Kantor et al. in 1997